## Phase 4 — Geo-Proximity Filter

**Goal**: "Near this photo" button in the Lightbox triggers a filtered grid view showing photos
taken within a configurable radius.

### Files to modify

#### `src/ui/web/src/components/Lightbox.tsx`

Add a "Photos nearby" button in the metadata sidebar, visible only when `gps_lat` and `gps_lon`
are non-null on the asset detail. Clicking navigates to BrowsePage with geo filter params:

```typescript
const handleNearbyClick = () => {
  const params = new URLSearchParams();
  params.set("near_lat", String(asset.gps_lat));
  params.set("near_lon", String(asset.gps_lon));
  params.set("near_radius_km", "1");
  navigate(`/libraries/${libraryId}/browse?${params}`);
  onClose();
};
```

Button placement: Below the GPS coordinates display in the metadata panel. Icon: a map pin or
crosshair. Style: secondary button matching existing metadata panel actions.

#### `src/ui/web/src/components/FilterBar.tsx`

Add a chiclet for active geo-proximity filter: "Within 1km of [lat, lon]" with a clear button.
Optionally add a radius selector (0.5km, 1km, 5km, 10km, 50km) that updates `near_radius_km`.

#### `src/ui/web/src/pages/BrowsePage.tsx`

Read `near_lat`, `near_lon`, `near_radius_km` from search params and pass to `pageAssets`.

### Acceptance criteria

- Lightbox shows "Photos nearby" button only when GPS data is available.
- Clicking the button closes the Lightbox and navigates to BrowsePage with geo filter active.
- The grid shows only photos within the specified radius.
